Natural Language Processing (NLP) is gaining significant traction across various industries due to its ability to understand, interpret, and generate human language. The market can be segmented based on different factors such as type, deployment mode, organization size, and application. In terms of type, NLP can be categorized into rule-based, statistical, and hybrid systems. Rule-based systems rely on predefined patterns, statistical systems use machine learning algorithms, while hybrid systems combine both approaches for more robust NLP solutions. Regarding deployment mode, organizations can choose between on-premises or cloud-based NLP solutions based on their requirements. Furthermore, NLP caters to organizations of all sizes, from small and medium-sized enterprises to large corporations. Finally, the application of NLP is extensive, covering areas like sentiment analysis, named entity recognition, machine translation, information extraction, question answering, and other functionalities.

